# 3D System — React Three Fiber + Drei

## Import rule: ALWAYS dynamic, NEVER SSR
```tsx
import dynamic from "next/dynamic";

const MyCanvas = dynamic(() => import("@/components/3d/MyCanvas"), {
  ssr: false,
  loading: () => <div className={styles.canvasPlaceholder} />,
});
```

## Standard Canvas setup
```tsx
import { Canvas } from "@react-three/fiber";
import { Float, Environment, ContactShadows } from "@react-three/drei";

<Canvas
  camera={{ position: [0, 0, 5], fov: 45 }}
  dpr={[1, 1.5]}          // cap pixel ratio for perf
  gl={{ antialias: true, alpha: true }}
  style={{ background: "transparent" }}
>
  <ambientLight intensity={0.4} />
  <directionalLight position={[5, 8, 5]} intensity={1.2} castShadow />
  <Float speed={1.4} rotationIntensity={0.4} floatIntensity={0.6}>
    <MyMesh />
  </Float>
  <Environment preset="studio" />
</Canvas>
```

## Material system (from `crochetMaterials.ts`)
- **Crochet material:** matte, slightly rough — use for toy body
- **Accent material:** mid-gloss — for accessories
- **Gloss material:** high specular — for eyes/buttons
Always import from `@/components/3d/crochetMaterials` — don't duplicate.

## Interaction patterns
```tsx
import { useFrame, ThreeEvent } from "@react-three/fiber";
import { useRef, useState } from "react";

// Hover rotation
const meshRef = useRef<THREE.Mesh>(null);
const [hovered, setHovered] = useState(false);
useFrame((_, delta) => {
  if (!meshRef.current) return;
  meshRef.current.rotation.y += delta * (hovered ? 0.8 : 0.2);
});
```

## Lazy load canvas (IntersectionObserver)
```tsx
const [show, setShow] = useState(false);
const ref = useRef<HTMLDivElement>(null);
useEffect(() => {
  const obs = new IntersectionObserver(([e]) => e.isIntersecting && setShow(true), { rootMargin: "200px" });
  if (ref.current) obs.observe(ref.current);
  return () => obs.disconnect();
}, []);
return <div ref={ref}>{show && <MyDynamicCanvas />}</div>;
```

## Performance rules
- `dpr={[1, 1.5]}` — never exceed 2× on mobile
- Dispose geometries and materials on unmount: `useEffect(() => () => geo.dispose(), [])`
- Use `<Suspense fallback={null}>` around heavy R3F scenes
- Merge geometries when rendering many identical objects

